"content": "In the age of computers, the world is a darker place than ever before. The air is thick with a sense of dread that's hard to shake off even when you want to forget about it. It's as if everyone has forgotten how to relax, let alone live. As a mother, I was raised to be one of the first lines of defense against this psychotic threat. My husband had worked at Bell Labs for over thirty years, and my son was in the field, so when my parents retired they asked me to take on the job of being their techno-psychologist."

